Working Module

The Smart Cleaning Robot operates as an autonomous system that integrates sensing, navigation, and cleaning mechanisms. The working process is divided into the following modules:

1. System Initialization
When powered ON, the Arduino initializes all components including sensors, motors, and display.
The system checks battery status and prepares for operation.

2. Obstacle Detection Module
Ultrasonic sensors (front and back) measure distance to obstacles.
IR sensors (left and right) detect nearby objects and edges.
The robot continuously monitors surroundings to avoid collisions.

3. Navigation Module
Based on sensor inputs, the robot decides movement:
Moves forward when path is clear
Turns left/right if obstacles are detected
Moves backward and changes direction if blocked
Ensures smooth and autonomous navigation.

4. Cleaning Module
The cleaning system operates simultaneously during movement:
Rotating brushes sweep dust toward the vacuum inlet
Vacuum unit collects dust and stores it in the dustbin
Water pump sprays water for wet cleaning
Wet wiping mechanism removes stains
Dry wiping mechanism dries the floor

5. Control Module
Arduino Uno acts as the central controller
Motor driver (L298N) controls wheel and brush motors
Relays/transistors control vacuum and water pump

6. Power Management Module
Powered by rechargeable batteries
LED display shows battery level
Charging port allows easy recharging

7. User Interface Module
ON/OFF button controls system operation
LED indicators show robot status
Front LED light enables operation in low-light conditions
Working Summary
Power ON the robot
Sensors scan environment
Robot moves autonomously
Cleaning mechanisms activate
Obstacles are avoided in real-time
Cleaning continues until task completion

Output
Efficient dust removal
Clean and dry floor surface
Reduced manual effort
Reliable and continuous operation
